title: ​ Democrats left with ‘egg on their face’ as government shutdown ends
description: 'Brad vs Everyone' podcast host Brad Polumbo mocks the Democrats' “absurd failure” as the US government shutdown ends and leaves the party with “egg on their face”.  “They caused weeks of suffering and chaos, made a whole little stand and accomplished nothing,” Mr Polumbo told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “They've earned a lot of political capital … what ultimately proved a futile stunt.” ​

title: Liberals have been ‘dismantling’ their party over net-zero
description: MST Financial Senior Energy Analyst Saul Kavonic says Australians have watched the Liberal Party “dismantling themselves internally” over the net-zero 2050 target.

title: ​ The ‘sweet moment’ Trump invites children into the Oval Office
description: 'Brad vs Everyone' podcast host Brad Polumbo reacts to an exchange at the White House where US President Donald Trump invites children into the Oval Office.  “It's a sweet moment, and I hope he showed them the Diet Coke button,” Mr Polumbo told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “It's good to see the lighthearted side of the presidency.  “We could all use some more positivity in the news cycle these days.”

title: The ‘failure’ of an energy policy under Chris Bowen
description: MST Financial Senior Energy Analyst Saul Kavonic says Minister for Climate Change and Energy Chris Bowen has changed on some “policies” where he is “talking a lot more positively about gas”.  Mr Kavonic told Sky News host Steve Price that Mr Bowen has made a “recognition that his previous stance, which was much more hostile to gas, was a failure”.  “Leading to increased costs and instability in the markets.”

title: Liberals ‘sitting on the fence’ with net zero
description: One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson says the Liberals’ plan to dump net zero is “not going to happen”.  Ms Hanson told Sky News host Rowan Dean that the party is “sitting on the fence”.  “They still want their emissions, they still want the Paris Agreement, they still want to address climate change.”

title: Net zero leads to the ‘destruction’ of Australia’s economy: Pauline Hanson
description: One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson says her party has “set the agenda” on net zero.  Ms Hanson told Sky News host Rowan Dean that net zero leads to the “destruction” of Australia’s economy.  “And what is happening to our industries, manufacturing rises in electricity cost.”

title: US population is ‘concerned’ about high immigration
description: One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson says the US is “concerned” about high immigration.  Ms Hanson told Sky News host Rowan Dean that US President Donald Trump has “taken control” of the country’s energy policy so climate issues are not a concern for Americans.  “A lot of the Americans actually came up to me after my speech and said it was a really good speech.”

title: Sussan Ley’s ‘real capability’ on display after bold move to ditch net zero
description: Former Liberal senator Hollie Hughes says Opposition Leader Sussan Ley has proven her leadership qualities by dropping net zero.  Ms Hughes told Sky News host Rowan Dean that the decision shows what she is “capable” of.  “I think you’re only going to see more of this and you’re going to see the real capability of a woman who’s a farmer, a single mum, who’s gone and done her tax degrees.”

title: Energy is ‘critical’ to much more than just electricity bills
description: MST Financial Senior Energy Analyst Saul Kavonic highlights that energy is “critical to much more” than just Australians’ electricity bills.  “It is critical to our manufacturing sector, it is critical to the reindustrialisation of our critical supply chains,” Mr Kavonic told Sky News host Steve Price.  “We need to regain our energy advantage again … that is what enables us to have high standards of living.”

title: ‘Very honoured’: Pauline Hanson talks about her experience speaking at Mar-a-Lago
description: One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson discusses her speech at Mar-a-Lago in the United States.  Ms Hanson told Sky News host Rowan dean that she was “very honoured” to be able to speak.  “We got so much in common with the American people.”

title: ADF need the ‘right technology’ to be able to defend the country
description: One Nation Leader Pauline Hanson says Australia needs to “increase” defence spending to maintain national security.  Ms Hanson told Sky News host Rowan Dean that “future years” could see high global tensions.  “And not that far down the track, we need to equip them with the right technology and equipment if we want them to defend our nation.”

title: The ‘idiotic’ net-zero policy is now ‘deceased’
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean calls the “deceased” net zero a “moronic, idiotic, half-witted” policy.  “Every Liberal and Coalition MP who supported the Net Zero disgrace should now hang their head in shame and hope the electorate soon forgets their imbecility,” Mr Rowan said.  “It was presented as a blatant threat akin to emotional blackmail, in my opinion.”

title: ​ TV Host pays tribute to the great ‘Richo’ Richardson
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean pays tribute to the “great” former Labor senator Graham Richardson, who died last week.  ​He’s one of the great people I've known in the media, and debating him was something I will sorely miss,” Mr Rowan said.  “Richo, we’ll all miss you.”

title: BBC’s ‘mess-ups’ only harm Trump and Republicans
description: Political Commentator Stephanie Hamill calls the BBC’s speech edit of US President Donald Trump “totally unethical”.  “The difference in the videos of what actually happened is just so egregious on so many levels,” Ms Hamill told Sky News host Rowan Dean.  “Notice how the mess-ups always go one way, and that is the direction in harming President Trump or Republicans. “The evidence is there.”

title: Democrats voted over a ‘dozen times’ to not reopen the government
description: Political Commentator Stephanie Hamill argues it’s the Democrats' “fault” for the longest US government shutdown, as they voted “over a dozen times” to not reopen.  “They made this as difficult as possible; they held the American people hostage, literally for no reason,” Ms Hamill told Sky News host Rowan Dean.  “If they want to have this healthcare debate, they need to have it separately … they shouldn’t just roll it into these big spending bills.”
